When you think about your iPhone

00:00:04.889 --> 00:00:08.354
It's probably the object that you use most than your life.

00:00:08.900 --> 00:00:12.813
It's the product that you have with you all the time.

00:00:13.071 --> 00:00:17.168
With this unique relationship people have with their iPhone

00:00:18.244 --> 00:00:20.850
We take changing it really seriously.

00:00:20.949 --> 00:00:26.509
We don't want to just make a new phone 
 we want to make a much better phone.

00:00:28.046 --> 00:00:30.845
iPhone 5 is the result of this approach.

00:00:31.309 --> 00:00:33.876
It's been completely redesigned.

00:00:34.416 --> 00:00:38.251
And for the first time ever we've increased the size of the Display.

00:00:39.549 --> 00:00:44.545
By making the screen taller but not wider 
 you can see more of your content

00:00:45.065 --> 00:00:47.076
but still comfortably use it with one hand.

00:00:47.967 --> 00:00:50.491
And yet even with the larger display

00:00:50.877 --> 00:00:55.693
iPhone 5 is the thinnest, lightest iPhone we've ever built.

00:00:56.866 --> 00:01:02.826
To achieve the design this thin we had to look at 
 making many of the components inside the design smaller.

00:01:03.206 --> 00:01:08.124
It's actually 18% thinner, 20% lighter than the previous iPhone.

00:01:08.124 --> 00:01:11.903
It took an incredible cross-collaborative effort to do this.

00:01:12.754 --> 00:01:16.491
From the beginning, we knew we want to bring LTE to the iPhone.

00:01:16.955 --> 00:01:22.292
What LTE does is that enables really fast downloads over your cellular network.

00:01:22.737 --> 00:01:26.874
You'll notice a big difference compared to previous network connectivity.

00:01:27.367 --> 00:01:32.712
In fact, LTE can actually be faster than the average WI-FI Connection at home.

00:01:33.201 --> 00:01:38.510
The conventional approach of designing LTE into a world phone uses 2 chips

00:01:39.010 --> 00:01:44.040
With the new iPhone, both voice and data 
 technology are combined onto a single chip.

00:01:44.547 --> 00:01:49.040
This is one of the real breakthroughs that enables iPhone 5's thin design.

00:01:49.981 --> 00:01:54.680
We're also introducing an all new Apple design A6 Chip.

00:01:55.159 --> 00:01:59.500
It delivers performance that is up to twice as fast as the previous generation.

00:01:59.880 --> 00:02:04.340
You'll experience a big increase in speed in everything you use your iPhone for.

00:02:04.858 --> 00:02:10.420
Especially in the way it delivers more detail and 
 boosts frame rates in graphics intensive apps.

00:02:11.224 --> 00:02:17.990
The A6 Chip is so power efficient that it 
 increases performance while also increasing its battery life

00:02:18.566 --> 00:02:23.530
Given that the dimensions of the new phone and 
 all the capabilities that we want to add.

00:02:24.032 --> 00:02:27.680
We needed to manage space inside the phone very carefully.

00:02:28.184 --> 00:02:31.200
We've created the new much smaller Lightning Connector.

00:02:31.205 --> 00:02:34.470
It's all digital, so it's designed for today's uses.

00:02:34.897 --> 00:02:37.830
and we made it Reversible so it fits either way.

00:02:38.995 --> 00:02:45.640
We've also moved to a Sapphire lens cover which is 
 thinner and more durable than previous cover glass.

00:02:45.642 --> 00:02:49.560
This really protects the optics and keeps your photos looking great.

00:02:50.012 --> 00:02:54.800
I don't think the level of Invention has ever 
 been matched by any other product we've done.

00:02:55.233 --> 00:03:00.840
The seamless integration between Hardware and Software makes everything you do on iPhone 5

00:03:01.297 --> 00:03:04.380
Just feel more Fluid, responsive and fast.

